sql:
SELECT evaluation_id
FROM model_evaluations
WHERE accuracy < 0.8 AND runtime_seconds > (
    SELECT AVG(runtime_seconds) FROM model_evaluations
);

SELECT model_id, COUNT(*) AS issues_count
FROM model_issue_reports
GROUP BY model_id;

SELECT *
FROM model_evaluations
WHERE runtime_seconds > (SELECT AVG(runtime_seconds) FROM model_evaluations);

SELECT model_id, AVG(runtime_seconds) AS average_runtime
FROM model_evaluations
GROUP BY model_id;

external_knowledge:
- "vast oceans of data" refers to datasets with sizes over 100MB;
- "analytical sharks" symbolizes classification models;
- "performance, measured by their F1 scores" indicates the evaluation metric used;
- "threshold of excellence" is metaphorically referring to the F1 score average above 0.7;
- "over the past year" signifies the period between '2022-01-01' and '2023-01-01';
- "embarked on downloading adventures" indicates that the access type was 'download'.

sql:
SELECT me.dataset_id, me.model_id, AVG(me.recall) AS avg_recall
FROM model_evaluations me
GROUP BY me.dataset_id, me.model_id;

external_knowledge:
- "shine brightly" metaphorically refers to high performance metrics (precision, recall, and accuracy);
- "beacon models" metaphorically refers to machine learning models;
- "light types" metaphorically refers to types of machine learning models (e.g., classification, regression);
- "threshold of 90%" metaphorically refers to an accuracy greater than 0.90;
- "runtime exceeding one minute" is directly related to the runtime_seconds being less than 60 seconds.
